result.name: Seorae

reviews.text: Very good Korean BBQ, kimchi had a lot of oomph and spice, the cooking plate was replaced very regularly, the meat was good quality, staff very friendly. Especially want to emphasize that they leave enough space between tables which creates a cozy atmosphere and allows private conversations over BBQ. At weekends they have long queues, I recommend booking in advance. We arrived with two people and got a table after a short wait. The smoke/smell management seems better than in other places. Can recommend!

The servers didn't really have time to check on us, and seating was limited for > 4 people. It was very hot where we were sitting and had to ask them to turn on the A/C, which they did. Otherwise pretty cool that they cook eggs on the side of the BBQ plate while the rest of your food cooks as well.
Authentic Korean fare. The staff are friendly and the prices are reasonable. Highly recommended.
Korean bbq can't miss. Good selection of grilling items from mushrooms and vegetables to beef and pork.    Meats are prepared and sliced and very tender and flavourful.
The pancake and fried chicken were pretty good. Not much service. And pricey for the quality.
